gomodel:SYNGO_2391  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Live imaging studies tracking the movement of Ti-VAMP positive vesicles in neurites of hippocampal neurons indicate the regulation of the velocity of motion of these vesicles when constitutively active or dominant negative Rab21 is over-expressed in these neurons.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods \"Human Q78L DCAAX Rab21 (amino acids 1-220) was cloned by PCR into pB6 as a C-terminal fusion to Gal4 DNA-binding domain.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-09" ;
